Office Depot obtains the categories of personal information listed above from the following categories of sources:

Direct interactions. You may give us your information by filling in forms or by corresponding with us by mail, phone, fax, email, webform, or in-person. This includes, but may not be limited to, personal data you provide when you:
Purchase our products;
Create a user account on our website;
Subscribe to our publications;
Request marketing be sent to you;
Interact with our website;
Interact with us, including through our website, app, or customer service;
 Interact with social media by visiting Office Depot pages, commenting on or liking posts;
Enter a competition, promotion, or survey; or
Provide information in-person at industry events or other venues, or providing information by phone, fax or email.
Automated technologies or interactions. As you interact with our website and app, we may automatically collect data about your equipment, browsing actions and patterns. We collect this personal data by using cookies and other similar technologies. Please click here for Office Depot's Cookie Policy  for further details about cookies and how to opt out.
Third parties or publicly available sources. We may receive personal data about you from various third parties and public sources as set out below:
Technical data from the following parties:
(a) Analytics providers such as Google;
(b) Advertising networks such as Google Adwords, Bing Adcenter, Amazon ads, and Criteo sponsored ads;
Data from providers of technical, payment and delivery services; and
Data from data brokers.

